Should work the same way both commands.
![2017-02-22 5](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2324012/23230532/a7ad8cc0-f944-11e6-8483-ab30cda3fff6.png)

```
function testHTTPObject1()
{
   WeatherFeed.delete(); // delete previous instances...
   
   // Create the HTTPObject
   %feed = new HTTPObject(WeatherFeed);

   // Define a dynamic field to store the last connection state
   %feed.lastState = "None";

   // Send the GET command
  %feed.get("httpbin.org:80", "/html", "");      

   // check executing in console: echo(WeatherFeed.buffer);
}

function testHTTPObject2()
{
   WeatherFeed.delete(); // delete previous instances...
   
   // Create the HTTPObject
   %feed = new HTTPObject(WeatherFeed);

   // Define a dynamic field to store the last connection state
   %feed.lastState = "None";

   // Send the GET command
   %feed.get("23.22.14.18:80", "/html", "");   
   
   // check executing in console: echo(WeatherFeed.buffer);
}

```
File to perform testings:
[httpExample.zip](https://github.com/GarageGames/Torque3D/files/794697/httpExample.zip)

